# /.MEMORY/.aidocs/index.aidocs

Session-start router only.

Read in order:
1. `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/global-instructions.aidocs`
2. `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/coding-standards.aidocs`
3. `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/memory-system.aidocs`
4. `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
5. `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`

Then open only task-relevant linked files.

Also available when needed:
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/research-safety.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/personality-system.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/CHANGELOG.md`

Command logic lives in global command packs, not in `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/`.
